@startuml
title Patrón Observador (Observer) - Django Signals

interface "Sujeto (Publisher)" as Subject {
  + add_observer(observer)
  + remove_observer(observer)
  + notify_observers(event_data)
}

class "Modelo User (Sujeto Concreto)" as User {
  + save()
}

interface "Observador (Subscriber)" as Observer {
  + update(event_data)
}

class "Signal Receiver (create_user_metrocoins)" as MetroCoinsReceiver {
  + update(sender, instance, created, **kwargs)
}

class "UserMetroCoins" as MetroCoinsModel {
  + create(user)
}

Subject <|.. User
Observer <|.. MetroCoinsReceiver

User -> MetroCoinsReceiver : 1. emite señal post_save
MetroCoinsReceiver -> MetroCoinsModel : 2. si created=True, crea perfil

note right of User
  **Patrón Observer (Publish/Subscribe)**
  Cuando ocurre un evento (ej. guardar un nuevo usuario),
  el Sujeto emite una señal a todos los observadores
  registrados (receivers) sin estar fuertemente
  acoplado a ellos.
end note
@enduml
